Add elevation range UX enhancements and bump to v1.2.1

Keyboard accessibility:
- Tab order through all legend controls (sliders, number fields, checkbox, opacity)
- Arrow keys move slider by 10m; Page Up/Page Down move by 100m
- role="group" + aria-labelledby on range section for screen readers

Direct number entry:
- Numeric input fields alongside each range slider
- Accepts any integer; clamped on Enter/blur; Escape cancels
- Spinner arrows hidden; styled to match dark legend panel

Mouse wheel fine-tuning:
- Scroll wheel on focused slider nudges value by 10m per tick
- Non-passive wheel listeners suppress page scroll while adjusting

Remember range checkbox:
- Persists Min/Max elevation to localStorage across sessions
- Store reads localStorage at init; falls back to defaults if missing
- Reset button updates localStorage when lock is active

Tests:
- ElevationLegend unit tests: 9 -> 28 (number inputs, keyboard, lock, axe)
- Playwright integration tests: 14 -> 27 (number input, keyboard nav, lock, reload restore)

Documentation:
- USER_GUIDE.md: keyboard table, number input, mouse wheel, lock checkbox sections
- FAQ.md: "Can I use keyboard?" and "How do I save my range?" entries
- QUICK-START-TUTORIALS.md: Tutorial 4 updated with all input methods
- KNOWN-ISSUES.md: removed 10m step size limitation (resolved by number entry + Page Up/Down)
- WelcomeTour.tsx: Analysis Tools step updated
- CHANGELOG.md: v1.2.1 section added
- docs/RELEASE_NOTES_v1.2.1.md: new release notes
- All installer/build configs, README, and doc version headers bumped to 1.2.1

